Package: redfire-gateway
Version: 1.0.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31), libssl3 (>= 3.0.0), systemd (>= 247)
Recommends: chrony, ntp, gpsd
Suggests: wireshark, tcpdump, asterisk
Maintainer: Redfire Telecommunications <support@redfire.tel>
Homepage: https://github.com/redfiretel/redfire-gateway
Description: TDMoE to SIP Gateway with Advanced Telecommunications Features
 Redfire Gateway is a comprehensive telecommunications gateway that bridges
 legacy Time Division Multiplexing over Ethernet (TDMoE) infrastructure with
 modern Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) and Voice over IP (VoIP) systems.
 .
 Key Features:
  * TDMoE interface support with advanced framing and error correction
  * SIP/SDP protocol handling with full RFC compliance
  * RTP media processing with codec negotiation
  * PRI (Primary Rate Interface) emulation for legacy ISDN integration
  * Sigtran/SS7 protocol support for mobile network interconnection
  * Advanced timing and clock synchronization (GPS, NTP, PTP, Stratum)
  * Comprehensive testing and monitoring capabilities
  * SNMP management interface
  * Real-time diagnostics and troubleshooting tools
  * High-availability and redundancy features
 .
 This package includes the main gateway daemon, command-line tools,
 configuration files, and documentation for deployment in carrier-grade
 telecommunications environments.